NDL II Solid Waste:
- Qaraoun: UNDP has completed the project and handed it over the Qaraoun Lake Union of Municipalities including 1) an awareness raising campaign in 5 villages in Qaraoun Lake Union of Municipalities, 2) the supply of the necessary 2,241 bins, 3) Construction and provision of equipment to the Qaraoun Storage Facility including: Steel Hangar, Diesel Generator, Vertical Baler, 2 Pick-up Trucks, Skid steer loader, Weighing Scale;
- North Bekaa: Following the request from the Ministry of environment, the project launched a Request for Proposal for conducting an EIA and a preliminary design for the construction of Sorting Facility and Sanitary Landfill for 9 villages in North Bekaa;
- Bar Elias: the design for the additional landfill cell is initiated, the construction is to follow;
- Hezzerta: UNDP is supplying the Municipality of Hezzerta with the needed refuse collection vehicle (8-10m3, with compactor); The project with the MoE, and in collaboration with the Municipality of Hezzerta has selected the environmental firm to undertake the necessary studies for a sustainable closure and rehabilitation of Hezzerta dumpsite;
- Training for Municipalities: The project has completed the development of 2 training Manuals for Municipal Police and Member of Municipal Council. The City of Tripoli was targeted as the first pilot area, where a training workshop was conducted over a period of 7 days and attended 40 persons.

